cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on understanding popularity evolution in social media, specifically on Facebook. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper explores the factors that influence popularity in social media. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon issues related to privacy and security in social media. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with collecting and analyzing a large dataset of posts and popularity values. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may involve analyzing multimedia content (e.g. images, videos) posted by professional users on Facebook.
